$$ {\text{VD}}_{i} ^{ * } = {\text{VD}}_{i} {\left( {u_{i} - {\text{VT}}} \right)}\quad {\text{if}}\;u_{i} \ge {\text{VT}}\quad {\text{else}}\;{\text{VD}}_{i} ^{ * } = 0 $$\end{document}Following suggestions of Tononi et al. (1992), the product of equation (2) was set equal to 0 when a membrane potential (ui) was less than a voltage threshold VT (set equal to 0.5). In that case, only a voltage-independent stimulus-related input determines the net input to the neuron, without any amplification.
